  "title": "Core Concepts of Understanding Cybersecurity",
  "lessonText": "This section introduces fundamental concepts essential for grasping the basics of cybersecurity.",
  "data": {
    "content": "• Cybersecurity involves protecting systems, networks, and data from digital attacks.\n• Key terms include:\n  - Threat: potential cause of an unwanted incident.\n  - Vulnerability: weakness in a system that can be exploited.\n  - Risk: potential for loss or damage when a threat exploits a vulnerability.\n• Understanding these concepts helps in identifying and mitigating cybersecurity risks.\n• Cybersecurity is crucial for safeguarding personal and organizational information."
  }
}
